{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603917","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603917"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:45:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:45:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15785"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15785","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15785"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8476"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62579"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8476","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8476"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15785"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48026"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"7061"},{"type":"tags","id":"8497"},{"type":"tags","id":"8499"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20377"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20379"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62579","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/62579"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA histological section of a seminiferous tubule is being examined under light microscopy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following correctly describes the histological appearance of a Sertoli cell?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Flattened cell with elongated nucleus in tubule wall","Polygonal cell with round nucleus and acidophilic cytoplasm","Tall columnar cell with irregular borders and pale oval nucleus","Small round cell with condensed chromatin and thin cytoplasm","Round cell with dark nucleus and prominent acrosome"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etall columnar cell with irregular borders and pale oval nucleus\u003C/strong\u003E correctly describes a Sertoli cell. These cells extend from the basement membrane to the lumen of seminiferous tubules and have distinctive pale, euchromatic nuclei with prominent nucleoli.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eround cell with dark nucleus and prominent acrosome\u003C/strong\u003E describes a spermatid. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eflattened cell with elongated nucleus in tubule wall\u003C/strong\u003E describes a peritubular myoid cell. The \u003Cstrong\u003Epolygonal cell with round nucleus and acidophilic cytoplasm\u003C/strong\u003E describes a Leydig cell. The \u003Cstrong\u003Esmall round cell with condensed chromatin and thin cytoplasm\u003C/strong\u003E describes a spermatogonium.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESertoli cells are essential supporting cells that provide structural support, nutrition, and factors necessary for spermatogenesis. They form the blood-testis barrier and regulate the microenvironment within seminiferous tubules.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Sertoli cells are tall columnar cells with irregular lateral borders that extend from the basement membrane to the lumen of seminiferous tubules.","Sertoli cells have pale, euchromatic nuclei with prominent nucleoli and provide structural and nutritional support to developing sperm cells."],"references":["Lara NLEM, Costa GMJ, Figueiredo AFA, de Fran\u00e7a LR. The Sertoli cell: what can we learn from different vertebrate models? Anim Reprod. 2020 May 22;16(1):81-92. doi: 10.21451/1984-3143-AR2018-125. PMID: 33299481; PMCID: PMC7720927.","Peng YJ, Tang XT, Shu HS, Dong W, Shao H, Zhou BO. Sertoli cells are the source of stem cell factor for spermatogenesis. Development. 2023 Mar 15;150(6):dev200706. doi: 10.1242/dev.200706. Epub 2023 Mar 20. PMID: 36861441; PMCID: PMC10112922.","Ansell, I. D. (2012). Atlas of male reproductive pathology (Vol. 10). Springer Science \u0026 Business Media.","Wong WJ, Khan YS. Histology, Sertoli Cell. [Updated 2022 Nov 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK560631/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48026"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15785"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48026","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48026"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-17T23:21:08+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-17T23:21:31+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8476"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62579"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagG